    <p>Re­cently, I no­ticed cig­a­rette butts all over the place, from cof­fee shops to pedes­trian path­ways.</p>
    <p>Per­haps a new cam­paign is needed to get smok­ers to ex­er­cise more care when dis­pos­ing of the butts. Such ir­re­spon­si­ble be­hav­iour runs counter to the clean and green so­ci­ety we strive for and is un­fair to clean­ers.</p>
